% Description Table
*FRAME TAP.THEO 0 0 2 0 0 0 1 		%Theoretical frame of Component. If a MAD-X is used it should be at the Entrance of the element. OK With That? Might be more complicated structure than that.
*FRAME TAP.BUMP 0 0 0 0 0 0 1 		%Can the offset be generated as a Bump from MAD-X? or there is it two different principles? Could be several Frame, depends on GEODE.
*FRAME TAP.REAL 0 0 0 0 0 0 1   	TX	TY	TZ	RX	RY	RZ	%Real measured Position of the TAP element? Could be 2 frames, depends of GEODE
%add beam points
*CALA 
BEAM_TAP.E 		0	0	0
BEAM_TAP_S		0	10	0
TAP.A.LONGI 	0 	1 	0.4
TAP.L.LONGI 	0 	9 	0.4
